channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: EC-SfM: Efficient Covisibility-based Structure-from-Motion for Both Sequential and Unordered Images
item.description: Based on this general image connection, we propose a unified framework to efficiently reconstruct sequential images, unordered images, and the mixture of these two.

item.title: Boosting the Power of Kernel Two-Sample Tests
item.description: The kernel two-sample test based on the maximum mean discrepancy (MMD) is one of the most popular methods for detecting differences between two distributions over general metric spaces.

item.title: Multi-Modal Self-Supervised Learning for Recommendation
item.description: The online emergence of multi-modal sharing platforms (eg, TikTok, Youtube) is powering personalized recommender systems to incorporate various modalities (eg, visual, textual and acoustic) into the latent user representations.

item.title: Lightweight-Yet-Efficient: Revitalizing Ball-Tree for Point-to-Hyperplane Nearest Neighbor Search
item.description: Finding the nearest neighbor to a hyperplane (or Point-to-Hyperplane Nearest Neighbor Search, simply P2HNNS) is a new and challenging problem with applications in many research domains.

item.title: Improving Scene Text Image Super-Resolution via Dual Prior Modulation Network
item.description: Scene text image super-resolution (STISR) aims to simultaneously increase the resolution and legibility of the text images, and the resulting images will significantly affect the performance of downstream tasks.

item.title: Valid Inference for Machine Learning Model Parameters
item.description: However, this can come with the risk of overtraining; in order for the model to generalize well, it is of great importance that we are able to find the optimal parameter for the model on the entire population -- not only on the given training sample.

item.title: Generic Dependency Modeling for Multi-Party Conversation
item.description: To model the dependencies between utterances in multi-party conversations, we propose a simple and generic framework based on the dependency parsing results of utterances.

item.title: CADIS: Handling Cluster-skewed Non-IID Data in Federated Learning with Clustered Aggregation and Knowledge DIStilled Regularization
item.description: By performing an in-depth analysis of the behavior of a classification model's penultimate layer, we introduce a metric that quantifies the similarity between two clients' data distributions without violating their privacy.

item.title: Assessing Domain Gap for Continual Domain Adaptation in Object Detection
item.description: To ensure reliable object detection in autonomous systems, the detector must be able to adapt to changes in appearance caused by environmental factors such as time of day, weather, and seasons.

item.title: Mean Parity Fair Regression in RKHS
item.description: We study the fair regression problem under the notion of Mean Parity (MP) fairness, which requires the conditional mean of the learned function output to be constant with respect to the sensitive attributes.

item.title: An Efficient Two-stage Gradient Boosting Framework for Short-term Traffic State Estimation
item.description: In particular, we present an efficient two-stage gradient boosting framework for short-term traffic state estimation.

item.title: Minimax-Bayes Reinforcement Learning
item.description: While the Bayesian decision-theoretic framework offers an elegant solution to the problem of decision making under uncertainty, one question is how to appropriately select the prior distribution.

item.title: On Calibrating Diffusion Probabilistic Models
item.description: In this work, we observe that the stochastic reverse process of data scores is a martingale, from which concentration bounds and the optional stopping theorem for data scores can be derived.

item.title: On ML-Based Program Translation: Perils and Promises
item.description: In the future, we envision an end-to-end program translation tool where programming domain knowledge can be embedded into an ML-based translation pipeline using pre- and post-processing steps.

item.title: ChatGPT: Jack of all trades, master of none
item.description: Our comparison of its results with available State-of-the-Art (SOTA) solutions showed that the average loss in quality of the ChatGPT model was about 25% for zero-shot and few-shot evaluation.

item.title: FrankenSplit: Saliency Guided Neural Feature Compression with Shallow Variational Bottleneck Injection
item.description: Lightweight neural networks exchange fast inference for predictive strength.

item.title: Bridging the Gap between ANNs and SNNs by Calibrating Offset Spikes
item.description: The experimental results show that our proposed method achieves state-of-the-art performance on CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100, and ImageNet datasets.

item.title: Adaptive Discretization using Voronoi Trees for Continuous POMDPs
item.description: ADVT uses the estimated diameters of the cells to form an upper-confidence bound on the action value function within the cell, guiding the Monte Carlo Tree Search expansion and further discretization of the action space.

item.title: Dual Policy Learning for Aggregation Optimization in Graph Neural Network-based Recommender Systems
item.description: This framework adaptively determines high-order connectivity to aggregate users and items using dual policy learning.

item.title: Co-Driven Recognition of Semantic Consistency via the Fusion of Transformer and HowNet Sememes Knowledge
item.description: Multi-level encoding of internal sentence structures via data-driven is carried out firstly by Transformer, sememes knowledge base HowNet is introduced for knowledge-driven to model the semantic knowledge association among sentence pairs.

item.title: Scalable Infomin Learning
item.description: The task of infomin learning aims to learn a representation with high utility while being uninformative about a specified target, with the latter achieved by minimising the mutual information between the representation and the target.

item.title: RecFNO: a resolution-invariant flow and heat field reconstruction method from sparse observations via Fourier neural operator
item.description: The MLP embedding is propitious to more sparse input, while the others benefit from spatial information preservation and perform better with the increase of observation data.

item.title: Escaping limit cycles: Global convergence for constrained nonconvex-nonconcave minimax problems
item.description: This paper introduces a new extragradient-type algorithm for a class of nonconvex-nonconcave minimax problems.

item.title: Toward Asymptotic Optimality: Sequential Unsupervised Regression of Density Ratio for Early Classification
item.description: Theoretically-inspired sequential density ratio estimation (SDRE) algorithms are proposed for the early classification of time series.

item.title: Nystr√∂m $M$-Hilbert-Schmidt Independence Criterion
item.description: In order to alleviate the quadratic computational bottleneck in large-scale applications, multiple HSIC approximations have been proposed, however these estimators are restricted to $M=2$ random variables, do not extend naturally to the $M\ge 2$ case, and lack theoretical guarantees.

item.title: Towards Unbounded Machine Unlearning
item.description: Deep machine unlearning is the problem of removing the influence of a cohort of data from the weights of a trained deep model.

item.title: A DNN based Normalized Time-frequency Weighted Criterion for Robust Wideband DoA Estimation
item.description: However, the best-performing design of T-F weights is criterion-dependent in general.

item.title: Can discrete information extraction prompts generalize across language models?
item.description: We study whether automatically-induced prompts that effectively extract information from a language model can also be used, out-of-the-box, to probe other language models for the same information.

item.title: What happens before and after: Multi-Event Commonsense in Event Coreference Resolution
item.description: Event coreference models cluster event mentions pertaining to the same real-world event.

item.title: Pseudo Label-Guided Model Inversion Attack via Conditional Generative Adversarial Network
item.description: At first, a top-n selection strategy is proposed to provide pseudo-labels for public data, and use pseudo-labels to guide the training of the cGAN.

item.title: Multiagent Inverse Reinforcement Learning via Theory of Mind Reasoning
item.description: To understand how people interact with each other in collaborative settings, especially in situations where individuals know little about their teammates, Multiagent Inverse Reinforcement Learning (MIRL) aims to infer the reward functions guiding the behavior of each individual given trajectories of a team's behavior during task performance.

item.title: Adaptive Sparse Gaussian Process
item.description: Next, to make the model inference as simple as possible, we propose updating a single inducing point of the sparse GP model together with the remaining model parameters every time a new sample arrives.

item.title: Improving User Controlled Table-To-Text Generation Robustness
item.description: In this work we study user controlled table-to-text generation where users explore the content in a table by selecting cells and reading a natural language description thereof automatically produce by a natural language generator.

item.title: Demonstration-Guided Reinforcement Learning with Efficient Exploration for Task Automation of Surgical Robot
item.description: Task automation of surgical robot has the potentials to improve surgical efficiency.

item.title: Because Every Sensor Is Unique, so Is Every Pair: Handling Dynamicity in Traffic Forecasting
item.description: Further analysis also shows that each pair of sensors also has a unique dynamic.

item.title: Cross-domain Compositing with Pretrained Diffusion Models
item.description: Diffusion models have enabled high-quality, conditional image editing capabilities.

item.title: Composer: Creative and Controllable Image Synthesis with Composable Conditions
item.description: Recent large-scale generative models learned on big data are capable of synthesizing incredible images yet suffer from limited controllability.

item.title: iQPP: A Benchmark for Image Query Performance Prediction
item.description: To date, query performance prediction (QPP) in the context of content-based image retrieval remains a largely unexplored task, especially in the query-by-example scenario, where the query is an image.

item.title: Fantastic Rewards and How to Tame Them: A Case Study on Reward Learning for Task-oriented Dialogue Systems
item.description: Prior works mainly focus on adopting advanced RL techniques to train the ToD agents, while the design of the reward function is not well studied.

item.title: Implementation of DNN Based Data Detector for QPSK Systems
item.description: For this system, a deep learning based detector was proposed and implemented alongside the conventional method.

item.title: Metropolis Theorem and Its Applications in Single Image Detail Enhancement
item.description: Traditional image detail enhancement is local filter-based or global filter-based.

item.title: Medical Face Masks and Emotion Recognition from the Body: Insights from a Deep Learning Perspective
item.description: This face occlusion can strongly irritate emotional reading from the face and urges us to incorporate the whole body for emotion recognition, as it needs to play a more major role, despite its complementary nature.

item.title: Take Me Home: Reversing Distribution Shifts using Reinforcement Learning
item.description: To aid in our estimates of Wasserstein distance, we employ dimensionality reduction through orthonormal projection.

item.title: Heterogeneous Social Event Detection via Hyperbolic Graph Representations
item.description: This model addresses the heterogeneity of social media, and, with this graph, the information in social media can be used to capture structural information based on the properties of hyperbolic space.

item.title: Incremental Few-Shot Object Detection via Simple Fine-Tuning Approach
item.description: In this paper, we explore incremental few-shot object detection (iFSD), which incrementally learns novel classes using only a few examples without revisiting base classes.

item.title: Interactive Face Video Coding: A Generative Compression Framework
item.description: In this paper, we propose a novel framework for Interactive Face Video Coding (IFVC), which allows humans to interact with the intrinsic visual representations instead of the signals.

item.title: A Novel Collaborative Self-Supervised Learning Method for Radiomic Data
item.description: We compared our proposed method with other state-of-the-art self-supervised learning methods on a simulation study and two independent datasets.

item.title: Gaussian processes at the Helm(holtz): A more fluid model for ocean currents
item.description: Oceanographers are interested in predicting ocean currents and identifying divergences in a current vector field based on sparse observations of buoy velocities.

item.title: HTNet: Human Topology Aware Network for 3D Human Pose Estimation
item.description: 3D human pose estimation errors would propagate along the human body topology and accumulate at the end joints of limbs.

item.title: CMVAE: Causal Meta VAE for Unsupervised Meta-Learning
item.description: Unsupervised meta-learning aims to learn the meta knowledge from unlabeled data and rapidly adapt to novel tasks.
